</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7E45F27EA989B922916853E63B98C0D2" pageId="290" pageNumber="291" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="CAD90AB063D963872AFBA8D6A7672C0B" pageId="290" pageNumber="291">
<taxonomicName id="A30F40CED45E93ADCDC989FA5A91D428" authorityName="Alluaud" authorityYear="1919" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Halocoryza" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="290" pageNumber="291" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Halocoryza</taxonomicName>
Alluaud, 1919: 100. Type species: 
<taxonomicName id="489D03CA1A57799E6CE5027A807C2168" authorityName="Alluaud" authorityYear="1919" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Halocoryza" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="290" pageNumber="291" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maindroni">
<emphasis id="FA662C45E8AFBCAE6CA33CBF8685912D" italics="true" pageId="290" pageNumber="291">Halocoryza maindroni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Alluaud, 1919 by monotypy. Etymology. From the Greek 
<emphasis id="E2EE074DB824BD6AF70FDD91688277F6" italics="true" pageId="290" pageNumber="291">halos</emphasis>
(sea) and generic name 
<taxonomicName id="765A4D5DF2195051FE4F9A0CEF33D728" authorityName="Putzeys" authorityYear="1866" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Coryza" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="290" pageNumber="291" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="217795ED4CB7056BE1439CF5355D0031" italics="true" pageId="290" pageNumber="291">Coryza</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, alluding to the presence along the sea (under &quot; 
<emphasis id="183DF797D85774359BFF308B7D0D29B0" italics="true" pageId="290" pageNumber="291">
de grosses pierres le long de la 
<normalizedToken id="B05D2AD2B6FAAA3D8264AE345746E8FA" originalValue="jetée">jetee</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
... 
<emphasis id="A6171ADF43672FEEC3D3BAD50B9C7ABA" italics="true" pageId="290" pageNumber="291">
ces pierres sont vraisemblablement 
<normalizedToken id="CA94B37B769BD33DE0C74BF5E2C2B681" originalValue="submergées">submergees</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="25255F08668486AFF689A6D5EE0A5A03" originalValue="à">a</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="0E17BC5FA60CA275316639939F37D9A9" originalValue="marée">maree</normalizedToken>
haute
</emphasis>
&quot;) of adults of these 
<taxonomicName id="990B1CD7B4123903CA4A5A700AA93FE1" authorityName="Putzeys" authorityYear="1866" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Coryza" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="290" pageNumber="291" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3682B75ACADAFD0B616FC8D2BDE492F5" italics="true" pageId="290" pageNumber="291">Coryza</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-like species [feminine].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2C1FCA79D610B57942812226E3C7D5E9" pageId="290" pageNumber="291" type="diversity">
<paragraph id="8E97F963941020AD02C9373486CE9E26" pageId="290" pageNumber="291">Diversity.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A014CAA422720074F3E62A7CA095F5D1" pageId="290" pageNumber="291">
Four species are placed in this genus: one (
<taxonomicName id="B3E94DDE01C6C4907BF68B9DEB058C62" authorityName="Whitehead" authorityYear="1966" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Halocoryza" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="290" pageNumber="291" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acapulcana">
<emphasis id="B7900FEB77C12B52CC2F242E3F8CEA99" italics="true" pageId="290" pageNumber="291">Halocoryza acapulcana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Whitehead) is found on the Pacific Coast of Mexico and on the 
<normalizedToken id="744200F204C83FC8A1140ECF8B146A5B" originalValue="Galápagos">Galapagos</normalizedToken>
Islands, one (
<taxonomicName id="62944D9ED2E7E68F706683DA1CD4AC70" baseAuthorityName="Darlington" baseAuthorityYear="1939" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Halocoryza" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="290" pageNumber="291" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arenaria">
<emphasis id="8E46E60374FFC164DDD9BDFC17D3020E" italics="true" pageId="290" pageNumber="291">Halocoryza arenaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) in southeastern North America, the West Indies, Brazil, and the west coast of Africa, another one (
<taxonomicName id="A3E2D21FA7B3C5493CB69236516A072E" authorityName="Alluaud" authorityYear="1919" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Halocoryza" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="290" pageNumber="291" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maindroni">
<emphasis id="768AD60311DFFEFC768B4899BC544776" italics="true" pageId="290" pageNumber="291">Halocoryza maindroni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Alluaud) on the east coast of Africa and several islands along the western part of the Indian Ocean, including Madagascar, and the southern part of the Red Sea, and the last one (
<taxonomicName id="7D6456E97E1BB3DB2A68BAFDE5D92101" authorityName="Erwin" authorityYear="2011" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Halocoryza" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="290" pageNumber="291" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="whiteheadiana">
<emphasis id="AEBDD45696079B4768AADB21B2AB2345" italics="true" pageId="290" pageNumber="291">Halocoryza whiteheadiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Erwin) on Baja California Sur.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="DAD9607BAFBAC4C4DCB13E81D27370F6" pageId="290" pageNumber="291" type="identification">
<paragraph id="69E29D861D52AF3923FC69D63B40A2E8" pageId="290" pageNumber="291">Identification.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B28CF6B49D72CF5EE2EF2426693E8797" pageId="290" pageNumber="291">Whitehead (1967) and Erwin (2011a) reviewed the species and provided keys for their identification.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
